  "text": "Through consultation from early stages of design through to construction and operation, we are able to advise our clients on how to best identify opportunities and manage potential impacts and from an environmental and engineering perspective. Responsibilities: Develop Client relationships and identify local and regional opportunities to secure Hydrogeology, Engineering Geology, and Contaminated Land scopes. Provide training and mentoring of team members, fostering of strong working relationships across Arup. Manage communications with Client and the Project Engineer to understand the project requirements and set clear scopes and budgets for delivery. You will need to take a longer -term strategic view of the business to contribute to the development plan of Arup. You will be responsible for executing responsibilities as outlined in Arup\u2019s Quality Management System You will be required to represent Arup at internal and external meetings.",
